Such an Inspiration .. I am a Zumba Fitness Instructor in the UK .. Since undergoing major breast cancer surgery 3 years ago.. I got back  to teaching my classes within 6 weeks of my mastectomy.. but with steroids and hormones.. ended up gaining 3 stone in weight  in the last 3 years .. despite 5 high intensity classes per week .. plus clean eating and lots  of walking ... I still have this same energy.. and a passion for dance fitness.. If you have a passion and can be an inspirational teacher... and obviously you love to dance ..,who says you have to conform to size ... If you’ve got it ... you’ve got it ...

I made the decision after seeing and doing this once that I would do this workout as my premier workout until I could do the whole thing through without stopping.  For me I've been told I need to lose weight because I'm slightly overweight for being 17 and 4'9.  I also have chronic ankle issues and arch issues which makes it hard to exercise in general.  I move the wrong way I might re-sprain my ankle and everything I do such as excessive standing causes severe pain in my arches.  But I don't like regular workouts cause I get bored fast.  This is entertaining and fun.  For the most part my ankle is fine but my arches always hurt when I do too much so I have to stop for a minute.  I figure eventually I will be able to go through the whole thing.  And I have been able to get a little further doing a little more advanced stuff each time.  I do this workout practically daily and I absolutely love it.  Because I can't wear orthotics/my afo's while doing this because I need to be able to move my ankles it takes a little longer.  But I enjoy this workout so much.  I have been doing it for almost 2 weeks straight now.  And I feel like it's been helping a lot.
